Field Detail

INGEST_SUBMIT

public static final java.lang.String INGEST_SUBMIT
IngestCommand is set in a batchFiles element


For an add...
type="NORMAL" (same as version one batchIngest without a command line), pid's are assigned when one at a time just prior to foxml ingest.
type="replyWithPid" Causes a respond immediately with the pids that will for all files contained in the batchIngest.xmlbatch file. The pid's are reserved and saved, in comments, within the split mets files and will be assigned at a later time, when the ingest actually happens. (this is used when performing a fedoraProxy ingest via a form post)

NOTE: the batchIngest.xml file may have any name, it just needs to be valid batch file with an .xml extension and reside in the work directory..


For an update... type="ALL" means update meta and pco's.
type="Meta" is the meta data for 1 or more data-steams with the elements.
type="PCO" means just attached objects (Primary contect objects).

isTask

public boolean isTask()
If true the ingest is running as a task ie the ectd task. A task runs on a background timer and takes two calls of the timer to complete the ingest. The first pass performs the ingest and saves the ingest and pid report to the taskTemp folder, the second pass finishes up by the processing files in the taskTemp folder and sending email's (if enabled) posting any required rest responses.

runningAsTask

public boolean runningAsTask(boolean runningAsTask)
Set to true when the ingest is running as a task, ie the ectd task. A task runs on a background timer and takes two calls of the timer to complete the ingest. The first pass performs the ingest and saves the ingest and pid report to the taskTemp folder, the second pass finishes up by the processing files in the taskTemp folder and sending email's (if enabled) posting any required rest responses.

NOTE: Setting this to false when running a task, or visa-versa, is UNDEFINED and UNPREDICTABLE.
